{"comments":"Depth of Field atoms — simulated camera focus effects.\n\n## Photographic Model\n\nDepth of field simulates how real cameras focus:\n\n- **Focal distance**: Distance at which objects are in sharp focus\n- **Aperture (f-stop)**: Size of lens opening. Lower = shallower DoF\n- **Bokeh radius**: Blur radius for out-of-focus areas\n\n## CSS Implementation\n\nCSS doesn't natively support depth-of-field. These atoms define the\nparameters that can be rendered via:\n\n- CSS `filter: blur()` on individual elements\n- WebGL post-processing shaders\n- Canvas 2D composition with blur\n- SVG filters with `feGaussianBlur`\n\n## Usage\n\n```purescript\nimport Hydrogen.Schema.Elevation.DepthOfField as DoF\n\n-- Define focus parameters\nconfig :: DoF.DepthOfFieldConfig\nconfig = DoF.depthOfFieldConfig\n  { focalDistance: DoF.focalDistance 500.0\n  , aperture: DoF.aperture 2.8\n  , bokehRadius: DoF.bokehRadius 8.0\n  }\n\n-- Calculate blur for an element at a given distance\nblurAmount = DoF.blurAtDistance config 800.0  -- returns blur radius\n```\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Elevation","DepthOfField"],"FocalDistance"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[145,52],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/DepthOfField.purs","start":[145,1]},"title":"eqFocalDistance"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Ord"],"Ord"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Elevation","DepthOfField"],"FocalDistance"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[146,54],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/DepthOfField.purs","start":[146,1]},"title":"ordFocalDistance"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Elevation","DepthOfField"],"FocalDistance"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[149,54],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/DepthOfField.purs","start":[148,1]},"title":"showFocalDistance"}],"comments":"Focal distance in pixels (or arbitrary units).\n\nRepresents the distance from the camera to the focal plane — where\nobjects appear sharpest. Objects closer or farther will be blurred.\n\nValues are clamped to >= 0 (negative distance is meaningless).\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"newtype","declType":"data","roles":[],"typeArguments":[]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[143,45],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/DepthOfField.purs","start":[143,1]},"title":"FocalDistance"},{"children":[],"comments":"Create a focal distance\n\nValue clamped to >= 0.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Elevation","DepthOfField"],"FocalDistance"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[154,41],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/DepthOfField.purs","start":[154,1]},"title":"focalDistance"},{"children":[],"comments":"Extract the focal distance value\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Elevation","DepthOfField"],"FocalDistance"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[158,44],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/DepthOfField.purs","start":[158,1]},"title":"getFocalDistance"},{"children":[],"comments":"Infinite focus — everything in focus (no DoF effect)\n\nRepresented by a very large distance where DoF effects are negligible.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Elevation","DepthOfField"],"FocalDistance"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[164,31],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/DepthOfField.purs","start":[164,1]},"title":"infiniteFocus"},{"children":[],"comments":"Close focus — shallow depth of field\n\nFocus on nearby elements, dramatic background blur.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Elevation","DepthOfField"],"FocalDistance"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[170,28],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/DepthOfField.purs","start":[170,1]},"title":"closeFocus"},{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Elevation","DepthOfField"],"Aperture"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[188,42],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/DepthOfField.purs","start":[188,1]},"title":"eqAperture"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Ord"],"Ord"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Elevation","DepthOfField"],"Aperture"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[189,44],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/DepthOfField.purs","start":[189,1]},"title":"ordAperture"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Elevation","DepthOfField"],"Aperture"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[192,37],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/DepthOfField.purs","start":[191,1]},"title":"showAperture"}],"comments":"Aperture (f-stop) value.\n\nControls depth of field shallowness:\n- Lower values (f/1.4, f/2.8): Shallow DoF, more blur\n- Higher values (f/11, f/16): Deep DoF, more in focus\n\nStandard f-stop scale: 1.4, 2, 2.8, 4, 5.6, 8, 11, 16, 22\n\nValues clamped to >= 1.0 (f/1.0 is the physical minimum).\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"newtype","declType":"data","roles":[],"typeArguments":[]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[186,35],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/DepthOfField.purs","start":[186,1]},"title":"Aperture"},{"children":[],"comments":"Create an aperture value\n\nValue clamped to >= 1.0.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Elevation","DepthOfField"],"Aperture"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[197,31],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Elevation/DepthOfField.purs","start":[197,1]},"title":"aperture"},{"children":[],"comments":"Extract the aperture f-stop value\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Elevation","DepthOfField"],"Aperture"],"tag":"TypeC